The banker wrung his hands. "I shall never see them again!" he cried. "And my son? You give me
hopes?"

"My opinion is in no way altered."

"Then, for God's sake, what was this dark business which was acted in my house last night?"

"If you can call upon me at my Baker Street rooms to-morrow morning between nine and ten I shall be
happy to do what I can to make it clearer. I understand that you give me carte blanche to act for
you, provided only that I get back the gems, and that you place no limit on the sum I may draw."

"I would give my fortune to have them back."